  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether routine sterile gloving can lower
      contamination rates in blood culture.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Because contamination during sampling for blood culture may interfere in interpreting the
      results of blood culture, lowering the contamination rates in blood culture is very
      important. According to current guideline, routine sterile gloving is not recommended. We
      hypothesized that routine sterile gloving can lower contamination rates in blood culture.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
